Hey Seth

Good questions â€” this stuff is a bit counterintuitive at first.

*Match score / intent score*
Itâ€™s not always best to filter strictly to the *highest* intent or match
score. In a lot of cases, that can actually over-constrain the audience and
hurt performance. We usually recommend testing a slightly broader range
rather than only the top tier.

*Custom Audience vs. Advantage+*
In most cases, youâ€™ll want to use these as *Custom Audiences*, not
Advantage+. Advantage+ tends to override a lot of the signal youâ€™re
intentionally injecting.
That said, you *can* split-test Custom Audience vs. Advantage+ if you want
to see how Meta handles expansion, but we generally start with Custom
Audiences only.

*Timeframe / refresh cadence*
This really depends on the buying behavior of the topic:

   -

   *Impulse or fast-decision offers* â†’ shorter intent windows
   -

   *High-consideration purchases* (e.g., cars, real estate, expensive
   services) â†’ longer intent windows, since people research for weeks or
   months before converting

Thereâ€™s no one-size-fits-all window â€” the key is matching the intent
timeframe to how long people realistically take to make a decision.

Happy to look at the specific vertical youâ€™re running and give a more exact
recommendation if helpful.


Thanks
Nate

FROM: Nate Calhoun <nate@retargetiq.com>

SUBJECT: Proposed Referral & Partnership Structure â€“ RetargetIQ / Agency Designs / Inbox Accelerator

Guys this was made with CHATGPT all % and commissions were randomly
generated by chat gpt and are simply placeholders. Let's set up a call to
figure out what would be fair to all parties.
------------------------------

Hey Ben, Alex â€”

Wanted to get everything clearly laid out in one place so we can align on
structure, referrals, and economics before formalizing this into a written
agreement.

Below is a *proposed framework* covering (1) equity clarification, (2)
agency partnerships, (3) retail referrals, (4) cross-referrals between
companies, and (5) direct referrals from Benâ€™s network. None of this is
final â€” the goal is to agree on direction and percentages so we can paper
it cleanly.
------------------------------
1. Equity Clarification (RetargetIQ)

To be explicit and documented:

   -

   Ben Munger and Munger Enterprises *formally resign and waive any and all
   rights* to the previously discussed *20% equity interest in RetargetIQ*.
   -

   No ownership, profit interest, or governance rights exist or will exist
   unless explicitly agreed to in writing in the future.
   -

   All future involvement is *strictly referral-based and/or service-based*,
   not equity-based.

This will be clearly stated in the final agreement for clarity and
protection on all sides.
------------------------------
2. Agency Clients â†’ Exclusive Partnership (Agency Designs)

*RetargetIQ Agency Users*

   -

   RetargetIQ has two customer types: *Agency* and *Retail*.
   -

   For *agency customers*, we propose an *exclusive referral partnership*
   with *Agency Designs*.

*How this works:*

   -

   When an agency signs up for RetargetIQ and needs:
   -

      White-label SEO
      -

      White-label websites
      -

      Fulfillment resources
      -

   We direct them to *Agency Designs* as our preferred / exclusive partner.

*Proposed commission:*

   -

   *10% monthly recurring commission* paid by Agency Designs to RetargetIQ
   -

   Commission applies for the life of the referred client
   -

   Applies only to services fulfilled by Agency Designs

*Support materials:*

   -

   RetargetIQ provides:
   -

      Platform walkthrough videos
      -

      Tutorials
      -

      Training assets
      -

   These can be embedded inside Agency Designsâ€™ program to support agencies
   using RetargetIQ.

------------------------------
3. Agency Designs â†’ RetargetIQ Referrals

*Reverse flow:*

   -

   If Agency Designs (Ben) refers an agency to RetargetIQ:
   -

      RetargetIQ pays *20% monthly recurring commission*
      -

      Applies to the RetargetIQ subscription
      -

      Paid for as long as the client remains active

------------------------------
4. Retail Clients â†’ Real SEO Proof (Profit Split)

*Retail Clients Defined:*

   -

   Non-agency end customers needing:
   -

      Websites
      -

      SEO
      -

      Ongoing marketing

*Proposed structure:*

   -

   RetargetIQ refers retail clients to *Real SEO Proof*
   -

   *Net profit split evenly* between:
   -

      Nathan
      -

      Alex
      -

      Ben

(Net profit to be clearly defined as revenue minus direct fulfillment
costs.)

*Reverse referral (Real SEO Proof â†’ RetargetIQ):*

   -

   If Real SEO Proof refers a client to RetargetIQ:
   -

      Proposed *15â€“20% monthly recurring commission*
      -

      Final % to be agreed on

------------------------------
5. Inbox Accelerator â†” Agency Designs â†” RetargetIQ Cross-Referrals

*Proposed baseline structure (open to adjustment):*

   -

   Agency Designs â†’ Inbox Accelerator: *20% recurring*
   -

   Inbox Accelerator â†’ Agency Designs: *10â€“15% recurring*
   -

   RetargetIQ â†’ Inbox Accelerator: *20% recurring*
   -

   Inbox Accelerator â†’ RetargetIQ: *20% recurring*

------------------------------
6. Direct Referrals From Benâ€™s Network (All Client Types)

We also want to clearly define *direct referrals from Ben personally*,
regardless of company.

*Scenario:*

   -

   If Ben refers someone from his personal or professional network directly
   to RetargetIQ â€” whether they are:
   -

      Agencies
      -

      Enterprise clients
      -

      Retail clients
      -

      Or any other deal type

We should establish a *standard referral commission* for those
introductions.

*Proposed structure (for discussion):*

   -

   *20% monthly recurring commission* on RetargetIQ subscriptions
   -

   Applies regardless of client category
   -

   Paid for the duration of the customerâ€™s active subscription
   -

   This is separate from Agency Designsâ€“specific referrals

Happy to adjust this if enterprise deals require different economics.
------------------------------
7. General Commission Terms (Proposed)

   -

   Monthly recurring commissions
   -

   Paid while the customer remains active and paying
   -

   No commission stacking unless explicitly agreed
   -

   Clear attribution rules
   -

   Either party may terminate referrals prospectively with written notice
   -

   No retroactive clawbacks

------------------------------
Next Steps

At this point, we really just need to:

   1.

   *Lock the commission percentages*
   2.

   Finalize *which relationships are exclusive*
   3.

   Agree on *definitions (agency vs retail, net profit, attribution)*

Once aligned, we can:

   -

   Create a *simple commission table* so everything is crystal clear
   -

   Track referrals via:
   -

      Dedicated calendar links, and/or
      -

      A shared tracking spreadsheet

From there, we formalize everything into a single clean agreement.

Let me know thoughts, changes, or pushback and weâ€™ll dial this in.

â€“ Nathan

Hi Greg!

Thank you for signing up! Please let me know if this will help you with any
questions you may have. If not I can make some custom loom videos regarding
specific questions or issues you may have. Below I added some helpful
information that can help get you familiar with the power of our platform.


*Walkthrough of Pulling Decision makers with a business email at single
family residential construction companies in the USA* - Watch Video
<https://www.loom.com/share/e95498633a014c6982e5ab95f68d0393>
<https://www.loom.com/share/e95498633a014c6982e5ab95f68d0393?utm_medium=gif>

In this video, I walk you through the process of building a B2B static list
specifically for construction companies, targeting decision-makers like
CEOs and VPs. I demonstrate how to filter by business email validation and
industry specifics to ensure we pull accurate data, ultimately generating a
list of around 11,000 records. I also emphasize the importance of cleaning
the data before any cold emailing efforts. Please make sure to utilize the
S.I.C. codes effectively and download the final list for your outreach
campaigns. Let me know if you have any questions as you work through this
process!

*Creating Targeted Audiences for Pest Control Marketing ðŸ“Š* - Watch Video
<https://www.loom.com/share/2ec17f0022a34d0c998ce21e6a3c47e6>
<https://www.loom.com/share/2ec17f0022a34d0c998ce21e6a3c47e6?utm_medium=gif>

In this video, I walked you through the process of creating an audience for
pest control inquiries from October 19th to 20th, which resulted in 125,000
records. I demonstrated how to download either the top 500 records or the
entire dataset. I also mentioned that the system will need a little time to
process the request before you can download the results. Please make sure
to check the saved queries for updates on your downloads. Let me know if
you have any questions!


Thank you,

Cindy

Why This Matters

Even on AudienceLabâ€™s highest tier, record caps still apply. With
Columbus-style intent data, itâ€™s easy to burn through millions of records

separate accounts per client, those caps become a real bottleneck. Our
platform has *no record limits*, even at scale.

What RetargetIQ Gives You

Identify previously anonymous website traffic and match those visitors to enriched consumer or business profiles.



2. Direct Mail Automation

Our large static B2B data setâ€”comparable to Apollo or ZoomInfoâ€”giving you firmographic profiles, contacts, and company data enriched and ready to export.

API Documentation

Next Steps

already have.  Most often we have at least a business name, address, and
